{"question_id": "Q003", "question": "Why does the English paper argue that what English is depends on context?", "ground_truth": "The paper argues that English can refer to different things in different contexts, such as a people, a spoken language, a codified system in grammars and dictionaries, or literature, so its meaning depends on the setting in which it is discussed.", "category": "definition_explanation", "difficulty": "medium", "policy": "maddpg_ceb", "data_source": "live_llm", "final_status": "accepted", "final_answer": "The English paper argues that what English is depends on context because the masked language model (MLM) training allows the representation to fuse both left and right context, enabling a deep bidirectional understanding of language. This approach ensures that the model maintains a contextual representation of every input token, which highlights the significance of context in determining meaning and interpretation.", "token_f1": 0.375, "rouge_l": 0.2178, "correctness": 0.375, "faithfulness": 1.0, "citation_support": 1.0, "source_precision": 0.0, "source_recall": 0.0, "verification_pass": 1, "unsupported_claims": 0, "latency_seconds": 13.4376, "num_llm_calls": 3, "token_usage": 4146, "num_steps": 4, "trace": [{"step": 1, "agent": "retriever", "action": "hybrid_rerank", "params": {"dense_sparse_weight": 0.5239579863846302, "top_k": 15, "rerank_threshold": 0.3663521409034729, "source_diversity": 0.46345730870962143}, "reward": -0.02, "done": false}, {"step": 2, "agent": "grader", "action": "loose_filter", "params": {"relevance_threshold": 0.6705119460821152, "evidence_keep_ratio": 0.49516642978414893, "strictness_score": 0.3345048129558563}, "reward": -0.07, "done": false}, {"step": 3, "agent": "generator", "action": "generate_short_answer", "params": {"temperature": 0.634782686829567, "citation_strictness": 0.462307907640934, "max_tokens": 720, "answer_detail_level": 0.2348664402961731}, "reward": -0.07, "done": false}, {"step": 4, "agent": 